%% Data Flow Diagram for kube-auth-proxy
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4/kube-auth-proxy.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as User Browser
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    participant OAuthSvr as OIDC/OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Upstream as Upstream Application<br/>configurable

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: OAuth2/OIDC Authentication (auth mode)
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/start<br/>HTTP/HTTPS (configurable)
    AuthProxy->>OAuthSvr: Redirect to authorize endpoint<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth2 client credentials
    Browser->>OAuthSvr: User login + consent<br/>HTTPS/443, User credentials
    OAuthSvr->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback?code=xxx<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, OAuth authorization code
    AuthProxy->>OAuthSvr: POST /token (code exchange)<br/>HTTPS/443, OAuth2 client + auth code
    OAuthSvr-->>AuthProxy: Access Token + ID Token
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Set-Cookie (session)<br/>302 Redirect to original URL
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /* (with session cookie)<br/>HTTP/HTTPS
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Forward request<br/>Auth headers forwarded
    Upstream-->>AuthProxy: Response
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Response

    participant Client as API Client
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Upstream2 as Upstream Application

    Note over Client,Upstream2: Flow 2: Kubernetes RBAC Authorization (rbac mode)
    Client->>RBACProxy: Request with Bearer Token<br/>HTTPS/8443, Bearer/X509
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authentication.k8s.io/v1/tokenreviews<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: TokenReview result (user identity)
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST /apis/authorization.k8s.io/v1/subjectaccessreviews<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: SubjectAccessReview result (allowed/denied)
    RBACProxy->>Upstream2: Forward request<br/>x-remote-user, x-remote-groups headers
    Upstream2-->>RBACProxy: Response
    RBACProxy-->>Client: Response

    participant SA as ServiceAccount Client
    participant AuthProxy2 as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP

    Note over SA,K8sAPI: Flow 3: K8s Service Account Token Validation
    SA->>AuthProxy2: Request with Bearer SA Token<br/>HTTP/HTTPS, Bearer Token
    AuthProxy2->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview<br/>HTTPS/443, SA Token
    K8sAPI-->>AuthProxy2: Token valid + identity
    AuthProxy2->>Upstream: Forward with auth headers

    participant Envoy as Envoy Gateway

    Note over Envoy,AuthProxy2: Flow 4: Envoy ext_authz Integration
    Envoy->>AuthProxy2: GET /oauth2/auth<br/>HTTP/4180, Bearer/Cookie
    AuthProxy2-->>Envoy: 200 OK (authorized) or 401/403 (denied)
